comments.body:
While researching if `Seek()` works correctly for drives on Windows, I can add a `FIXME` note and skip the detection with a
```go
if runtime.GOOS == "windows" {
    // FIXME: it is uncertain how Windows handles Seek() for block devices
    return
}
```

Is that acceptable too?

I am also wondering if it is even possible to provision volumes with `VolumeMode: Block` on Windows?

